milestones.description: John Davison and Ian Billcliff's 37-run partnership is CAN's highest for the 3rd wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 23 between Chumney and Ian Billcliff
Joe Harris and Abdool Samad's 23-run partnership is CAN's highest for the 7th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 9 between Ashish Bagai and Joe Harris
Codrington and Ashish Patel's 20-run partnership is CAN's highest for the 9th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 13 between Sanjayan Thuraisingam and Codrington
Seebaran and Ashish Patel's 23-run partnership is CAN's highest for the 10th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 21 between Davis Joseph and Codrington
John Davison has scored 2 fifty-plus scores in ODIs, the most for CAN breaking Ian Billcliff's record
Seebaran has conceded the most runs in an innings (61) in ODIs for CAN, going past Sanjayan Thuraisingam's record of 53
Ashish Bagai has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (6) for CAN, going past Ian Billcliff

stories.title: New Zealand pour on the runs, but fate out of their hands
stories.summary: New Zealand set out to score 197 runs in 16 overs as their first goal against Canada at the World Cup match in Benoni today, but the pressure was too much and they had to settle for a five-wicket win after 23 overs
